----Git---

Git --> It's used to track of code change and collaborate tool.

1.How to create GitHub account?
	github.com

2.How to configure Git in our local machine?
	Download git and install it on local machine

3.How to access git from our local machine?
	Genrate ssh from local machine

		    ssh-keygen -t rsa -b 4096 -C "your_email@example.com"

		-t rsa: Specifies the RSA algorithm for key generation.
		-b 4096: Sets the key length to 4096 bits for stronger security (recommended).
		-C "your_email@example.com": Adds a comment to the public key for identification.

	After creating the key, copy the key from below path in our local machine.
			userhomedir/.ssh/id_rsa.pub
	
      Add the key to Github server.
			go > your copilot > SSH & GPG Keys > create new key > Give title name and paste the key you copied from our local machine.

4.How to config repo in our local machine?
	Two ways--> https & ssh

		HTTPS
			git config --global user.name "Your Name"
			git config --global user.email "your.email@example.com"
		    git config --global credential.helper store
		SSH
			Step 3 for ssh configure.

5.How to copy the brach in our local machine?
		git clone "repo url"

6.How to add file?
	create or modified files > add > commit > push or pull
	u-untracked file (new)
	m-modified file

7.How to convert our local folder to git?
	git init
		create new repo
	git remote add origin "repo url"

8.How to branch cmds?
	git branch --->Current branch
	git branch -a --->List all braches
	git branch -m viji --->rename the branch name from main to viji
	git branch viji ---->new branch creation
	git checkout main --->Switch the branch

		
	
		
